==French==
===Etymology===
Alteration of Old French ''[[soulegier]]'', from Vulgar Latin ''*subleviare'', from Classical Latin ''[[sublevare]]'', from ''[[sub-'' + ''[[levare]]''.
===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/sulaʒe/}}
*{{SAMPA|/sulaZe/}}

===Verb===
'''soulager'''

# {{transitive}} to [[relieve]], [[soothe]]
#:*''C'est le soir qui '''soulage''' / Les esprits.''  It's the evening which soothes the spirits.  — Baudelaire, 'Le Crépuscule du Soir'
# {{reflexive}} to make oneself feel better, find relief

